text: Natalie Harrowell (9 February 1990 â€“ 10 December 2019) was an English rugby league player who played in the first-ever Women's Super League Grand Final in 2017. Harrowell played for Featherstone Rovers and was regarded as a "key member of the women's club team", she also held 3 caps for England Rugby League. She was admitted to the hospital with a virus and died during December 2019. ==References== ==Other websites== *https://www.mirror.co.uk/news/uk- news/rugby-league-star-killed-virus-21088733 Category:1990 births Category:2019 deaths Category:English rugby league players
